# Terraform Rules

- Never destroy existing infrastructure without explicit confirmation.
- Run `terraform plan` and review drift before any `apply`.
- Keep configurations idempotent and safe for repeated runs.
- Avoid hardcoded environment values; use variables and tfvars.
- Export critical resources through outputs for downstream tooling.
- Use clear resource naming aligned with environment and service role.
- Prefer incremental changes over broad refactors in live environments.
